+### P16: Razorpay Webhook Reliability (added 2026-05-09 — incident-driven)
+The Razorpay webhook receiver `/api/payments/webhook` is the canonical activation path. When verify (the fast path) fails, the webhook is the safety net. Both must be defended:
+
+1. **No 4xx may EVER be returned to a Razorpay webhook from middleware.** Razorpay retries 5xx with backoff but treats 4xx as **terminal** — a single 429/401/403/404 from middleware silently drops the event forever. The route handler may return 4xx (e.g. 400 for bad signature) because that's a real protocol error; middleware-level rejections are a regression.
+2. **`/api/payments/webhook` MUST be exempt from the general rate limiter.** Razorpay's webhook IPs are shared across merchants and easily exhaust 200 req/min. The exempt block in `src/proxy.ts` must remain BEFORE the general `checkRateLimit('general:...')` call, alongside `/api/v1/health`. The Razorpay HMAC signature check inside the route handler is the actual auth boundary.
+3. **`payment_webhook_events` is the canary.** If the table receives zero rows for >2 hours while `payment_history` has activity, webhooks are being silently dropped. The `/api/cron/payments-health` cron (10-min cadence) catches this shape and writes a `severity='critical'` ops_event.
+4. **Idempotency lives in the RPC.** Webhook handlers route through `activate_subscription_locked`, `atomic_subscription_activation_locked`, `atomic_cancel_subscription`, `atomic_downgrade_subscription`, or `record_webhook_event` — never raw two-statement UPDATEs. Re-delivery must be a no-op (or an explicit dedupe return).
+
+Incident reference: 2026-05-09 — `payment_webhook_events` empty for ~2 weeks before discovery; captured ₹699 payment for hridaankaushik307@gmail.com never activated. Root causes: (a) middleware 429 on webhook, (b) verify 401 from stale Supabase JWT after Razorpay popup interaction. Both fixed in commit `d5880ae1`.
+
+Critical files: `src/proxy.ts` (rate-limit exempt block), `src/app/api/payments/webhook/route.ts`, `src/app/api/payments/verify/route.ts`, `src/hooks/useCheckout.ts` (token re-grab before verify), `src/lib/payment-verification.ts`, `src/app/api/cron/payments-health/route.ts`, `src/app/api/cron/reconcile-payments/route.ts`.
+
+Regression coverage: `src/__tests__/payment-webhook-rate-limit-exempt.test.ts`, `src/__tests__/checkout-token-refresh.test.ts`. Hook enforcement: `post-edit-check.sh` flags any edit to `proxy.ts` that drops the webhook reference.
+
+### P17: Pending-Subscription Lifecycle Hygiene (added 2026-05-09 — incident-driven)
+Every RPC that writes a `student_subscriptions` row in `status='pending'` MUST clear lifecycle fields on the `ON CONFLICT (student_id) DO UPDATE` branch. A "pending" row is by definition a fresh subscribe attempt — it must never inherit state from a prior subscription generation.
+
+Fields that MUST be reset (NULL or 0) when transitioning back to pending:
+- `cancelled_at`, `cancel_reason` — otherwise the billing UI shows "Cancellation Scheduled" on a brand-new pending sub.
+- `current_period_start`, `current_period_end`, `next_billing_at` — otherwise the UI shows expired dates.
+- `amount_paid`, `renewal_attempts`, `grace_period_end`, `ended_at` — otherwise stale telemetry pollutes ops dashboards.
+- `razorpay_payment_id` — that field belongs to a completed prior charge.
+
+The `activate_subscription` RPC already does this on the activation path; `create_pending_subscription` was missing it before 2026-05-09. Hook enforcement: `post-edit-check.sh` flags any redefinition of `create_pending_subscription` that drops `cancelled_at = NULL` from the conflict branch.
+
+Critical RPCs: `create_pending_subscription`, `activate_subscription`, `activate_subscription_locked`, `atomic_subscription_activation_locked`. Migration reference: `20260509130000_create_pending_subscription_clear_stale_lifecycle.sql`.
+
 ### P14: Review Chain Completeness
 When a critical file is modified, mandatory downstream reviewers must be invoked before the task can be marked complete. The PostToolUse hook (`review-chain.sh`) injects reminders automatically. Orchestrator validates at Gate 5. Quality rejects if chains are incomplete. The full matrix is defined in `.claude/skills/review-chains/SKILL.md`.
 
