+## Razorpay Webhook Reliability (P16/P17 — 2026-05-09)
+
+Source: 2026-05-09 production incident (hridaankaushik307@gmail.com — captured ₹699 never activated). Two independent middleware/UX bugs combined: (a) `proxy.ts` general rate limiter returned 429 to Razorpay's webhook IPs, (b) Supabase JWT rotated during the Razorpay popup leaving useCheckout's captured token stale → /verify 401. Razorpay treats 4xx as terminal so the webhook safety net was also lost. `payment_webhook_events` table empty for ~2 weeks before discovery.
+
+| # | Test name | Asserts | Location | Status |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| REG-65 | `webhook_rate_limit_exempt_in_proxy` | `src/proxy.ts` contains the exempt block `pathname === '/api/payments/webhook'` AND that block sits BEFORE the general `checkRateLimit('general:${ip}', ...)` call. Removing the exemption (or moving it after the limiter where it would be dead code) fails the test. Also asserts `/api/v1/health` exemption is preserved and that cron endpoints are NOT exempt. Pins P16. | `src/__tests__/payment-webhook-rate-limit-exempt.test.ts` | E |
+| REG-66 | `useCheckout_refreshes_session_before_verify` | `src/hooks/useCheckout.ts` re-grabs `supabase.auth.getSession()` within ~800 chars BEFORE every `fetch('/api/payments/verify', ...)` call site, AND every such call uses `credentials: 'include'`. Closes the stale-JWT 401 vector observed when the Razorpay popup stays open >60s and Supabase rotates the access_token. Both subscription and order checkout paths are pinned. Pins P16 (verify path resilience). | `src/__tests__/checkout-token-refresh.test.ts` | E |
+
+### Operational backstop
+
+- `/api/cron/payments-health` (10-minute cadence, `vercel.json`) writes a `severity='critical'` `ops_events` row when `payment_webhook_events` receives zero rows for ≥2h while `payment_history` has activity in the same window — exactly the silent-drop shape from this incident.
+- `post-edit-check.sh` warns if `proxy.ts` loses the `/api/payments/webhook` reference, or if `create_pending_subscription` is redefined without `cancelled_at = NULL` on the conflict branch.
+- Migration `20260509130000_create_pending_subscription_clear_stale_lifecycle.sql` codifies P17 at the DB layer.
+
+### Invariants covered by this section
+
+- P11 (payment integrity — verified payment must produce verified entitlement)
+- P16 (Razorpay webhook reliability — never return 4xx from middleware)
+- P17 (pending-subscription lifecycle hygiene — fresh pending must not inherit stale fields)
+
+**Total: 37 entries — TARGET 35 EXCEEDED (incident-driven adds REG-65/REG-66).**
+
